    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-17T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="267"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/57a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-17T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. For Braden. Inasmuch as the change of government in Bolivia was effected by a
                        <hi rend="italic">coup d’état</hi> without any semblance of conformity to
                    the constitution, the Department believes that recognition is necessary. The
                    Busch régime has already given evidence of its desire to honor its international
                    engagements. Upon receipt of information that the Busch régime is maintaining
                    public order and is effectively administering the Government, and after
                    consultation with the other governments represented upon the Chaco Committee,
                    this Government will probably proceed at once to give consideration to according
                    recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
